@node Scenario_Plugins_Terrain " Scenario Terrain Plugin "
@{b}TERRAIN PLUGIN@{ub}

The Terrain plugin generates a fractal landscape.

@{b}Width@{ub} Sets the horizontal subdivisions.
@{b}Height@{ub} Sets the vertical subdivisions.
@{b}Steepness@{ub} Determines how steep the the generated landscape is. High
   values give a very steep terrain and low values result in gentle hills.
@{b}Waterlevel@{ub} Sets the water level of the landscape. Low levels give a
   very little water, high values give a landscape with much water and some
   islands.
@{b}Random seed@{ub} Sets the starting seed value for the random generator.
   Each different value leads to a different landscape.
@endnode

@node TipsTricks " Tips & Tricks "
@{b}TIPS & TRICKS@{ub}

@{b}General@{ub}
- RayStorm renders faster if you don't use planes, because intersections
  with planes cannot be calculated with the octree (helpfull in scenes with
  motion blur or soft shadows).

@{b}Scenario@{ub}

- @{b}The 020-Version of Scenario crashes!@{ub}
  In Kickstart V40.x, there is a bug in mathieeesingbas.library - it uses FPU
  code on non-FPU machines for division/multiplication. This bug can be easily
  fixed with a patch from Aminet: @{i]util/boot/PatchMathSB10.lha@{ui}
- @{b}I have problems with the screen refresh, the scene is only refreshed
  behind the requester!@{ub}
  Open the @{"MUI-settings" link Menu_Settings_MUI} requester and select from the window
  part for "Refresh" the "Smart"-mode.
- @{b}How can I change the texture and brush names without removing and adding
  them again?@{ub}
  Select @{"View->Show->Show Textures" link Menu_View_ShowTextures} or @{"View->Show->Show Brushes" link Menu_View_ShowBrushes}
  and select the texture or brush. Now open the @{"settings-requester" link Menu_Object_Settings} and change
  the name of the brush or texture.
- @{b}How can I change the name of an RSOB/TDDD/LWOB/3DS/RAW-object without deleting
  and reloding it?@{ub}
  Select @{"Settings" link Menu_Object_Settings} from the object menu of the parent axis. Here you
  can change the name of the object.
- @{b}How can I load my old Imagine attribute files to use it for RayStorm
  objects?@{ub}
  Load the attributes file with @{"load object" link Menu_Object_Load}. You will get an axis
  named 'Mesh' with another axis attached to it. The surface of this axis is set
  to the attributes of the file. Click with the right mouse button to the parent
  axis and select @{"To scene" link Object_Menus}. The parent axis is no deleted
  and can now open the attributes requester for the child axis. Select save from
  the @{"attributes requester" link Menu_Object_Attributes} and save the surface as a RayStorm material file.
- @{b}If I apply a checker texture to a plane looks noisy!@{ub}
  If the texture is exactly on the plane, the color of the texture jumps
  between black and white because of rounding errors. Try to move the texture
  axis a little (e.g. 0.02) away from the plane.
- @{b}How can I switch on shadows?@{ub}
  You must turn off Quick Rendering in Render settings. In addition to that turn
  on cast shadows in the light settings.
- @{b}Depth of Field doesn't seem to work. I changed the aperture and the focal distance,
  but nothing happens.@{ub}
  You must increase the antialiasing value >1.

@{b}RayStorm Script@{ub}
- The commands '@{"TEXTUREPATH" link TEXTUREPATH}', '@{"OBJECTPATH" link OBJECTPATH}' and '@{"BRUSHPATH" link BRUSHPATH}' are relative
  to the directory RayStorm is started from.
- If RayStorm crashes with scenes with reflections and transparence, try
  to start RayStorm with a larger stack (e.g. 8192 bytes or more).
@endnode

